{"parentUuid":"3a2227ad-9bfd-4754-9782-30915166034e","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01HxXcSQc8uQUpd8EiXemyuc","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**Mutex** — exclusive lock. One thread owns it at a time. Only the owner can unlock it. Used to protect a single shared resource.\n\n**Semaphore** — a counter. Initialized to N, it allows up to N threads to enter concurrently. Any thread can signal (increment) it, not just the one that waited.\n\nKey differences:\n\n| | Mutex | Semaphore |\n|---|---|---|\n| Concurrency | 1 (binary) | N (counting) |\n| Ownership | Yes — only owner unlocks | No — any thread can signal |\n| Use case | Mutual exclusion | Limiting concurrency (e.g. connection pool of 10) |\n\nA binary semaphore (N=1) looks similar to a mutex but lacks ownership semantics — any thread can release it, which makes it unsuitable for protecting critical sections where you need strict lock/unlock pairing."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":35794,"cache_read_input_tokens":10131,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":35794},"output_tokens":31,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"}},"requestId":"req_011CZPVGMGiDHrCo5iE8Wvgs","type":"assistant","uuid":"ff2c09e6-ec04-4a12-8179-eee66ee97310","timestamp":"2026-03-25T08:32:33.955Z","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain-v1/el-paso-v1","sessionId":"1d3a5b1c-05cd-4d2d-896e-8039d8d23abd","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"marcus-sa/sandbox-agent-eval"}
